claim.claim-text:
2. A method of protecting an electronic device from impacts comprising:
providing a protective cover formed from an elastomeric material that has a predetermined hardness, wherein said predetermined hardness is approximately 50 Shore A, and wherein said elastomeric material is silicone;
providing reduced thickness portions of said protective cover that have a first predetermined thickness;
providing raised impact portions of said protective cover that have a second predetermined thickness that is greater than said first predetermined thickness, wherein said first predetermined thickness is approximately 0.6 mm and said second predetermined thickness is approximately 1.5 mm;
providing recesses in corner portions of said protective cover that allow said protective cover to compress and absorb impacts at said raised impact portions, wherein said recesses have a width, length, and height of approximately 4 mm, 2 mm, and 0.7 mm, respectively; and
providing ribs between said recesses, wherein said ribs have a thickness of approximately 0.7 mm.
